Dia. 01 Black's territory doesn't change
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par If Black plays at 1, there is no change in his territory.
\par Black 1 only takes away White's possibility to make points.
\par
\par Therefore the \cf1\b counting method is simple\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par
\par }
