W[sr]
Dia. 03 2 Points
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par The value of White \'a1\'e2 stone is 2 points.
\par There is one point at X and White doesn't have to capture at A either.
\par So one extra point is added, which means \cf1\b 2 points\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par When the value of a move is counted, it is important to pay attention whether a defending move is needed or not.
\par
\par
\par }
